	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Lords and Ladies pray atten!<BR>
<BR>
In many posts you mention dragon scales yet not all of these are for the quests you seek.<BR>
Only certain specific scales are used for wurmslayer yet some of these others are used for Epic class quests I.E. Severilous of emerald jungle is a green specifically for the warrior epic and Nezeka of burning wood for the bard Epic.<BR>
<BR>
There are 3 scales used in the wurmslayer quest.<BR>
the X. scale can be aquired one of 2 ways, the first is to get the piece of Tektite from one of the named gargoyles in Overthere Outpost town by giving him the carnelian stones he needs to replace his eye.  Returning the tektite with a periodot to the named elf form of X. in temple of solusk ro you recieve one of your scales. (it is lore but NOT no drop) The rare version of this is X. in his dragon form spawning (an extremely rare occasion almost as bad as waiting for something like Rahotep on the Tallon Zek Server but I digress)<BR>
The other two scales need for wurmslayer are the G. scale and A. scale.  The names elude me at this time so please bare with.  The dragons G. and A. are much sought after and farmed regularly at the levels of around 45 a piece.  The scales at least on the Tallon Zek Server go for an average of 1k pp to 1.5k pp depending on how well you wheel and deal.  <BR>
<BR>
IN THE INTEREST OF SIR HOBBLE <BR>
Some people have complained of him running like a mad man with his buddy killing and being killed.  My advice in making this work is simple <BR>
1. Those of goodly races can track him I.E. druid, ranger, Sense-Coolguy spell to locate him.<BR>
SOW is quite important due those two being faster than SOW.  <BR>
<BR>
2. When you do cut these two off at the pass taget and hand off the items.  Unless these two have stopped that is the only way of slowing them up long enough to finish the quest.<BR>
<BR>
Wait couldn't we just mez, hold, snare, root, or something like that?  BAD IDEA! But I leave it in your capable hands.<BR>
<BR>
Frozenheart Evermoore<BR>
Knights of the Faceless<BR>
Destroyer of worlds<BR>
Bringer of pain<BR>
<BR>
Tallon Zek<BR>
 
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
